pageType: content
background:
  type: solid
  color: "$background"
elements:
  - elementId: top-bar
    elementType: shape
    bounds: [0, 0, 1280, 6]
    shapeName: rect
    fill:
      type: solid
      color: "$primary"
  - elementId: title
    elementType: text
    bounds: [60, 18, 1100, 38]
    content:
      style: "$actionTitle"
      align: [left, middle]
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>Five-Point Roadmap Targets Explainability, Regime Adaptation, and Accuracy</p>
  - elementId: divider
    elementType: shape
    bounds: [60, 58, 1160, 1]
    shapeName: rect
    fill:
      type: solid
      color: "$border"
  - elementId: roadmap-table
    elementType: table
    bounds: [60, 72, 1160, 220]
    columnWidths: [0.22, 0.12, 0.12, 0.12, 0.42]
    rowHeights: [0.16, 0.16, 0.16, 0.16, 0.16, 0.20]
    style: "$default"
    rows:
      - - content: {text: "Upgrade"}
        - content: {text: "Impact"}
        - content: {text: "Effort"}
        - content: {text: "Timeline"}
        - content: {text: "Description"}
      - - content: {text: "LightGBM + SHAP"}
        - content: {text: "High"}
        - content: {text: "Medium"}
        - content: {text: "Q3 2026"}
        - content: {text: "Replace HistGradientBoosting with LightGBM for native SHAP TreeExplainer support, enabling granular per-prediction feature attribution and faster training."}
      - - content: {text: "External Features"}
        - content: {text: "High"}
        - content: {text: "High"}
        - content: {text: "Q4 2026"}
        - content: {text: "Add competitor ad spend, market indices (Dow Jones, NASDAQ), and promotional calendars as exogenous inputs to capture regime changes before they appear in historical data."}
      - - content: {text: "Hierarchical Forecasting"}
        - content: {text: "Medium"}
        - content: {text: "Medium"}
        - content: {text: "Q4 2026"}
        - content: {text: "Implement top-down or bottom-up reconciliation so platform-level forecasts (Google, Meta, Bing) sum to campaign-type forecasts (Search, Pmax, Shopping)."}
      - - content: {text: "Online Learning"}
        - content: {text: "Very High"}
        - content: {text: "High"}
        - content: {text: "Q1 2027"}
        - content: {text: "Deploy incremental model updates that absorb new data daily without full retraining, enabling real-time adaptation to structural shifts and reducing forecast latency."}
      - - content: {text: "LLM Upgrade"}
        - content: {text: "Medium"}
        - content: {text: "Low"}
        - content: {text: "Q3 2026"}
        - content: {text: "Migrate from Gemma 2B to GPT-4o or Claude Sonnet for more nuanced, grain-name-aware narratives with deeper causal reasoning and richer business context."}
  - elementId: details
    elementType: text
    bounds: [60, 310, 1160, 370]
    content:
      fontSize: 16
      color: "$text"
      fontFamily: "Liter"
      lineHeight: 1.5
      align: [left, top]
      text: |
        <p><strong>1. LightGBM + SHAP (Q3 2026):</strong> Current permutation importance is model-agnostic but computationally expensive and coarse. SHAP values provide exact, per-prediction feature contributions that align with economic intuition. Expected outcome: 20% faster training and explainability that business stakeholders can trust.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:8px"><strong>2. External Features (Q4 2026):</strong> The Feb 2026 regime change was invisible to the model because it relied solely on internal historical data. Adding competitor spend (via SEMrush/SpyFu), market indices, and promotional calendars would give the model early warning signals. Expected outcome: 15-25% improvement in coverage rate during regime changes.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:8px"><strong>3. Hierarchical Forecasting (Q4 2026):</strong> Current forecasts are generated independently at platform and campaign-type levels, creating internal inconsistencies. Hierarchical reconciliation ensures Google + Meta + Bing forecasts equal the sum of Search + Pmax + Shopping forecasts. Expected outcome: elimination of contradictory recommendations.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:8px"><strong>4. Online Learning (Q1 2027):</strong> Full retraining is too slow for a market with monthly regime shifts. Incremental updates (e.g., River, scikit-learn partial_fit) would allow the model to adapt within days. Expected outcome: coverage rate maintained above 70% even during volatile periods.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:8px"><strong>5. LLM Upgrade (Q3 2026):</strong> Gemma 2B produces correct but templated narratives. GPT-4o or Claude Sonnet would generate more context-aware explanations that reference industry-specific concepts and produce board-ready language. Expected outcome: 40% reduction in narrative editing time for stakeholder communications.</p>
  - elementId: source
    elementType: text
    bounds: [60, 692, 1100, 18]
    content:
      style: "$caption"
      align: [left, middle]
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>Source: AIgnition Strategic Recommendations, Model Improvement Roadmap</p>
  - elementId: page-num
    elementType: text
    bounds: [1170, 692, 50, 18]
    content:
      style: "$caption"
      align: [right, middle]
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>14</p>
